.TH MKTEMP 1 "April, 2026"

.SH NAME
\fBmktemp\fP \- create temporary files and directories

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmktemp\fP [\fB\-d\fP] [\fB\-u\fP] [\fB\-q\fP] [\fItemplate\fP]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a temporary file or directory and prints its name.
.PP
Supported options:
.TP
.B \-d
Create a directory rather than a file.

.TP
.B \-u
Dry\-run: Print the name, but do not create the file.

.TP
.B \-q
Quiet: Do not print the generated filename. In combination with \fB\-u\fP, the
exit status can be used to determine if \fItemplate\fP was an accepted
template for
.IR mktemp (3).

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
1
\fItemplate\fP was not a permissible template string, or another error occurred.

.TP
0
A temporary filename was generated and, without \fB\-u\fP, created successfully.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mktemp (3)
